            "content": "# Claude Code Usage Status Line\n\nA status line extension for [Claude Code](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code) that shows session info and API usage percentages.\n\n```\n[Claude 4 Opus] $0.42 | 12m 30s | ctx: 45% | 32k in / 8k out | 🟢 5h: 12.3% 🟢 7d: 8.1% (Fri 3pm)\n```\n\nShows: model name, session cost, duration, context window usage, token counts, 5-hour and 7-day API usage with color indicators (🟢 < 50%, 🟡 50-80%, 🔴 > 80%) and next reset time.\n\nUsage data is fetched from the Anthropic API in the background every 60 seconds and cached locally.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- **macOS** (uses Keychain for credential access)\n- **jq** (`brew install jq`)\n- **curl**\n- **Claude Code** (logged in at least once so credentials exist in Keychain)\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/atermenji/claude-statusline-extra/master/install.sh | bash\n```\n\nOr clone and run locally:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/atermenji/claude-statusline-extra.git\ncd claude-statusline-extra\n./install.sh\n```\n\nThe installer will:\n1. Download `statusline.sh` and verify its SHA256 checksum\n2. Install it to `~/.claude/statusline.sh`\n3. Configure `~/.claude/settings.json` with the statusLine entry\n\nRestart Claude Code after installation.\n\n## Uninstall\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/atermenji/claude-statusline-extra/master/install.sh | bash -s uninstall\n```\n\nOr if cloned:\n\n```bash\n./install.sh uninstall\n```\n\nThis removes `~/.claude/statusline.sh`, the usage cache, and the `statusLine` entry from `~/.claude/settings.json`.\n\n## What gets installed\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `~/.claude/statusline.sh` | The status line script invoked by Claude Code |\n| `~/.claude/settings.json` | Updated with `statusLine` configuration (existing settings preserved) |\n| `~/.claude/usage_cache.json` | Created at runtime — cached API usage data |\n\n## Security\n\nThe installer verifies the downloaded `statusline.sh` against an embedded SHA256 checksum before installation. Downloads use HTTPS with TLS 1.2+ enforced.\n\nThe `statusline.sh` script reads Claude Code OAuth credentials from the macOS Keychain to query the Anthropic usage API. The installed script is set to `chmod 700` (owner-only access) and uses `umask 077` to restrict cache file permissions. Auth tokens are passed via `curl --config -` to avoid appearing in process listings.\n\nFor manual verification before running:\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/atermenji/claude-statusline-extra/master/statusline.sh -o statusline.sh\ncurl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/atermenji/claude-statusline-extra/master/SHA256SUMS -o SHA256SUMS\nshasum -a 256 -c SHA256SUMS\n```\n\n## Updating the checksum\n\nWhen modifying `statusline.sh`, regenerate the checksum files:\n\n```bash\nshasum -a 256 statusline.sh > SHA256SUMS\nshasum -a 256 statusline.sh | cut -d ' ' -f 1\n# Update EXPECTED_SHA256 in install.sh with the hash above\n```\n",
